<div class=" bubble" id="comment-43928">
  <blockquote>
    <p>I&#8217;ve used this method camping for years and generally speaking it works out very well.  Couple of secrets for the people that aren&#8217;t having success:</p>
<p>1.  More butter.  It does tend to add some taste and crispness, but greatly reduces the burning of the actual cookie.</p>
<p>2.  Less heat.  My stove is at the absolute lowest temperature that I can get it when I do this.  </p>
<p>As an aside, I have also successfully cooked this way with ready-bake cookies that are just spooned out of a roll.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <cite>
 <strong> Michael Fielden</strong>
